<TITLE> Polish president backpedals on NATO-Russia remarks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Helsinki, April 10 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Polish President Lech Kaczynski sought on Thursday to soften his remarks linking EU partnership talks with Russia with Georgia's and Ukraine's future membership in NATO. Kaczynski told Reuters in an interview on Wednesday that before the partnership talks start, Poland would like to see agreement inside the EU on whether the two former Soviet nations would receive a clear path towards NATO membership. Asked at a news conference during a visit to Helsinki if Poland was setting such a condition to lift its veto of the EU-Russia talks, Kaczynski said: "There was not such a formulation (in the interview). I said that we should consider this ... I said that we should not rush with the (EU-Russia) talk
